The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 September is 74,190 (8,550.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 1,548 new confirmed cases (178.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 September, there were 1,898 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (350 fewer cases).
